ratings.comment: Zane Li is a good lecturer and everything will make sense if you go to class. Don't need to read the textbook, but the class follows it. Practice exams are the best way to prep for midterms and final.
Nice professor. Not too hard to get an A.

He's a pretty good professor. While I wish I could've gotten a better grade, I don't blame Zane for anything. PLEASE UNDERSTAND THE MATERIAL WELL!! Grading criteria sucks as 86% of your grade is based on 3 exams. Unreasonably difficult to get an A but that's more of the math department's fault. Tl;dr: Zane is cool, UW Math dept. not so much.

Zane is an incredibly passionate prof. But his lectures weren't amazing. His pace would jump around a lot and he often ignored explaining what the topic we were learning actually is, especially line integrals at the end of the curriculum, just jumping right into theorems. He tends to spend too much time writing long theorems than doing examples.
He is so niccccccccccce! The one of best professor I ever met! He is good at teaching and explaining the difficult things!

While the class material was difficult, Li made it actually understandable. He was an engaging lecturer, willing to explain topics further/answer questions, clearly passionate about math. Tests were mostly out of his control due to the structure of the class, but he made an effort to help us be prepared. Also good w/ working w/ accommodations
